<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">April 22, 2024</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-april-22-2024/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-236059 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/American_Dictionary_of_the_English_Language_1828-150x150.jpg" alt="american dictionary of the english language" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400">​​</span><a href="https://daily.jstor.org/websters-dictionary-1828-annotated/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">On the first edition of Noah Webster’s </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">American Dictionary of the English Language</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400">.</span></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.publicbooks.org/a-theory-of-america-mythmaking-with-richard-slotkin/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">An interview with author and historian Richard Slotkin</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.theparisreview.org/blog/2024/04/19/on-the-distinctiveness-of-writing-in-china/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The unique experience of writing in China</span></a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-april-22-2024/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
